comments.body:
@rhatdan 
I'm not aware of the CI situation of this repo, but unit/integration tests could be introduced that check when the `add` functions are invoked, that only when a Windows container image is being built, expected PAX headers are added, and added files are put under the `files/` directory of the rootfs.

As of right now, performing add operations on a Windows container image on a Linux build system is completely broken, so while full end to end testing would be preferred, adding this and testing through unit tests would be an absolute positive addition.
